parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to a risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The ignition switch can short-circuit
causing the dashboard to catch on fire
destroying the vehicle. The ignition switch can also fail to turn off
causing the vehicle to continue running even when the key is removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to a risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The alternator can catch on fire
causing smoke and flames to emerge from under the hood. The battery light may come on after the alternator fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to a risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The electrical system can short-circuit
causing the vehicle to catch fire. The malfunction can also cause the vehicle to stall and jerk while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to complete recall work or issues with the recall process can lead to continued safety risks for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships may deny or delay recall work
or owners may experience difficulties scheduling appointments for recall work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to total loss, and pose a risk to the driver and occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire
often suddenly
with smoke or flames visible from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failures can cause engine overheating, leading to damage, stalling, or even engine fires.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
stalls
or jerks while driving
with possible signs of coolant leakage or failure of the water pump or fan belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition and electrical system issues can cause stalling, difficulty starting, or engine fires.
symptoms: The engine stalls
dies
or has difficulty starting
with possible signs of ignition system failure or electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system failures can cause engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine fires.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences decreased engine performance
noise
or exhaust leaks
with possible signs of catalytic converter or oxygen sensor failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to lock or retract
becomes extremely tight
sticks or gets stuck
does not come across the shoulder when the door is closed
does not release
or breaks
causing injuries or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic shoulder belt can cause injuries or accidents, as the belt may not properly restrain the occupant in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The automatic shoulder belt becomes extremely tight
sticks or gets stuck
does not come across the shoulder when the door is closed
or does not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt system can cause injuries or accidents, as the belt may not properly restrain the occupant in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The motorized seat belt system remains or locks up in the forward position
the hinge at the top end gears has stripped
the motor turns with no effect
or the entire system needs replacing.
